# Prefer object constants over string-literal unions

Avoid defining “magic string” union types directly (e.g. `type Severity = "info" | "warn"`).

## Rule

- Define a **`const` object** (not an array) with `as const`
- Derive the type from the object values
- Use the exported object values elsewhere to avoid typos

## Example

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
export const SEVERITY = {
  Info: "info",
  Warn: "warn",
  Error: "error",
} as const;

export type Severity = (typeof SEVERITY)[keyof typeof SEVERITY];

// Usage:
// severity: SEVERITY.Warn
```

```ts
// ❌ BAD
export type Severity = "info" | "warn" | "error";
```
